The paper deals with the problem of tracking a group of mobile nodes, which involves coordination, communication, and resource allocation among the nodes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The paper also deals with the use of wireless communication and signal processing techniques for tracking, which suggests that it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper proposes a new algorithm that takes into account the topology and resource availability of the group, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of clustering and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the energy-accuracy trade-off of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
